<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="252" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Distribution.</emphasis>
Jordana 
<emphasis box="[458,516,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">et al.</emphasis>
(2004) consider 
<taxonomicName box="[714,839,152,176]" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Schaefferia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="czernovi">
<emphasis box="[714,839,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">S. czernovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a Siberian species. Current records show that its distributional range covers northeastern part of Europe and north of West and Middle Siberia (
<figureCitation box="[1236,1320,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="6.[151,250,962,984]" captionTargetBox="[165,1427,394,928]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[150,1436,373,940]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 11. Map of species distribution. Black dots—Schaefferia czernovi, soil; grey dots—Schaefferia czernovi, caves; empty dot—Schaefferia bermani sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608302/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). There is also one published record of the species on 
<collectingRegion box="[655,764,223,248]" country="Russia" name="Chukotka" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Chukotka</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Babenko, A. B. &amp; Chernova, N. M. &amp; Potapov, M. B. &amp; Stebaeva, S. K." box="[780,1017,223,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" refId="ref4677" refString="Babenko, A. B., Chernova, N. M., Potapov, M. B. &amp; Stebaeva, S. K. (1994) Collembola of Russia and adjacent countries. Hypogastruridae. Nauka, Moscow, 336 pp. [in Russian]" type="book" year="1994">
Babenko 
<emphasis box="[891,942,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">et al</emphasis>
. 1994
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Babenko, A. &amp; Fjellberg, A." box="[1030,1346,223,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" refId="ref4727" refString="Babenko, A. &amp; Fjellberg, A. (2006) Collembola septentrionale. A catalogue of springtails of the Arctic regions. KMK Scientific Press Ltd, Moscow, 190 pp." type="book" year="2006">Babenko &amp; Fjellberg, 2006</bibRefCitation>
), which appears to be erroneous or at least in need of confirmation but the specimen is currently unavailable.
</paragraph>
